          "order": 2,
          "title": "FAST REAL-TIME VIDEO ENHANCEMENT",
          "summary": "ReBotNet is a video model that is designed to enhance live streams and video conferences in real-time. They use a dual-branch network that learns different types of video abstractions like location and time based ones. They then use a common decoder network to output the enhanced frames. It runs at 50 fps, uses about 5gb of memory and performs on par with models 8x larger.",
